<HEADLINE> Colorful Activities Mark 50th Birthday of Inner Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HUHHOT, July 20 (Xinhua) -- The art troupe that has come with
the central government delegation staged its debut here this
evening, as part of the celebrations to mark the 50th anniversary
of the founding of the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, China's
first ethnic-minority autonomous region.
</P>
<P>
Among the 1,000 audience was Vice-Premier Zou Jiahua, head of
the delegation, along with other delegation members.
</P>
<P>
Also this evening, delegation members joined a fireworks
evening party.
</P>
<P>
This afternoon, members of the central delegation went to the
local People's Park to joint gala activities with local people.
</P>
</TEXT>
