<HEADLINE> Pantani Wins His Second Stage in Tour de France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Marco Pantani of Italy won the 15th
stage of the Tour de France covering 208.5 kilometers from
Courchevel to Morzine on Monday.
</P>
<P>
This is the second victory in three days for the 27-year-old
mountain ace to climb to the third place.
</P>
<P>
The 14th stage winner Richard Virenque of France finished
second. Third place went to German Jan Ullrich, who retained the
overall leader's yellow jersey for the sixth day running.
</P>
<P>
Tuesday's 16th stage of 181km is from Morzine to Fribourg in
Switzerland. 
</P>
