<HEADLINE> OPEC's Supervised Oil Price Picks Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The average package price of seven
supervised oil products of the Organization of Petroleum Exporting
Countries (OPEC) last week picked up to 17.72 U.S. dollars per
barrel, OPEC secretariat's statistics showed today.
</P>
<P>
The average oil price was 17.58 dollars two weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
The average price in whole June was 17.37 dollars. The first
week of July saw a clear climb of the price to 17.92 dollars, but
it fell to 17.58 dollars in the following week.
</P>
<P>
The OPEC ministerial meeting in late June asked its member
states to strictly abide by their own daily quota, so as to
maintain the OPEC daily quota of 25.03 million barrels to
stabilize the world oil price. The stipulated OPEC oil price was
set at 21 dollars per barrel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
