<HEADLINE> Three Olympic Teams to Play China Four-nation Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Brazil, Argentina and host China,
all three participated in the Atlanta Olympics last year, will
play a four-nation men's basketball tournament slated from August
5-9 in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The tournament, with a total prize of 100,000 U.S. dollars,
will also be joined by the United States AIA team, which is
composed of players from NCAA and CBA.
</P>
<P>
In the Atlanta Olympic men's basketball competition, Brazil
finished sixth, while China took eighth, with Argentina ninth.
</P>
<P>
The tournament also serves as host team's warm-up for the Asian
Basketball Championship in September in Saudi Arab. 
</P>
