<HEADLINE> Global Mergers Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 21 (Xinhua) -- International company mergers and
acquisitions were up 9 percent for the first half of the year,
according to a study by KPMG Peat Marwick, a U.S. consulting
company.
</P>
<P>
Companies announced 130 billion U.S. dollars in cross-border
deals the first six months of 1997, as against 119 billion U.S.
dollars in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
But KPMG said that the record 284 billion U.S. dollars in
deals set last year could fall this year if global markets keep
their strong pace.  
</P>
</TEXT>
