<HEADLINE> Yeltsin to Cut Armed Forces by 500,000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
said today Russia will cut the size of the armed forces by 500,000
to 1.2 million by the end of 1998.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Defense Minister Igor Sergeyev at the
Volzhsky Utyos resort in central Russia where the president is on
holiday, Yeltsin said that efforts should be made to ensure stable
demobilization of the servicemen, the Itar-Tass news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
He promised that 100,000 houses will be built for retired army
officers.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin said that the number of generals of the army would be
limited within 2,300, adding Russia will continue its efforts to
built a professional army through military reform.
</P>
<P>
He said Russia must create "a mobile army equipped with
advanced weaponry," denying that the army reduction would weaken
the country's defense ability.
</P>
<P>
Sergeyev said the military reform is necessary so that the army
can increase its combat effectiveness. 
</P>
</TEXT>
