<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asian World Cup Finals to Be Played on Home and away Basis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- FIFA, world soccer governing body,
decided on Monday that a home and away format will be used in the
final Asian World Cup qualifying round.
</P>
<P>
Kuala Lumpur, Bahrain and Singapore had bid to hold a finals
tournament as in past Asian qualifying competitions.
</P>
<P>
But FIFA's World Cup Organising Committee, chaired by Lennart
Johansson, decided against a single tournament venue on Monday at
Zurich, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia and South Korea, who played in the 1994 World Cup,
were seeded. They will be kept apart when two groups of five teams
are drawn on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The other eight who will go into Tuesday's draw are China,
Iran, Kazakhstan, Japan, Kuwait, Qatar, United Arab Emirates and
Uzbekistan.
</P>
<P>
The winner and the runner-up in each group will qualify for the
semi-finals and the two semi-final winners will play the final and
also qualify for the World Cup finals in France next year.
</P>
<P>
The two losing semi-finalists will compete in a 3rd place
play-off, the winner of which will qualify for France. The losers
will play Australia, the Oceania Zone winners, on a home and away
basis for a berth in France.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
