described the airlines as a "new bridge across the Pacific" and
said it would help accelerate exchanges and cooperation between
peoples of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
About 100 representatives from local communities were present
to greet the flight crew and a 60-member Chinese delegation aboard
the airplane, which was led by Zhang Hanqin, vice-chairman of the
Standing Committee of the Guangdong Provincial People's Congress.
