<HEADLINE> Macao Wraps Up Celebrations for HK's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The special organization on the
celebrations of Hong Kong's return to China in Macao wrapped up its
work today following a series of activities which have
lasted for more than 20 days.
</P>
<P>
Ma Man Kei, executive chairman of the Presidium of the Macao
Compatriots' Preparatory Committee for the Celebration of Hong
Kong's Return to the Motherland, which was founded on April 1,
said that "the series of joyful activities were characterized with
happiness and unity, and demonstrated that Macao's compatriots
paid great attention to Hong Kong's return and are confident of
the concept of 'one country, two systems'."
</P>
<P>
Ma Man Kei said that the celebrations have increased Macao
residents' confidence in the "one country, two systems" policy.
</P>
<P>
The return of Hong Kong and the establishment of the HKSAR are
"a major historical event of international significance," he
said. "It will have a positive impact on Macao's return to China
and the final settlement of the Taiwan issue."
</P>
<P>
He called on Macao residents to get prepared for the handover
of power in Macao in less than two and half years.
</P>
<P>
Macao residents "should make an ever greater effort in
promoting the basic law of Macao, in pushing forward the
localization of civil service, of law and the use of Chinese as an
official language, help revive the economy and get prepared for a
smooth handover of power," he said.  
</P>
