<HEADLINE> Financial Business Expanding in Fujian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, July 21 (Xinhua) -- By the end of June this year bank
deposits in east China's Fujian Province reached 221.6 billion
yuan, up 31.4 billion yuan compared with the beginning of this
year.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, loans amounted to 159.6 billion yuan, a rise
of 12.9 billion yuan. The insurance business grew continuously,
with income reaching 1.8 billion yuan, up nearly 49 percent over
the first half of last year.
</P>
<P>
The People's Bank of Fujian Province said that the province's
increase of deposits was higher than the national average, and
local financial institutions poured more loans into state-owned
industries, agriculture and township enterprises in the first six
months. 
</P>
