<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pudong Records Steady Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The Pudong New Area in this
leading industrial city of China witnessed steady economic growth
in the first half of this year, with GDP topping 25.692 billion
yuan, up 17.7 percent over same period of the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Local statistics show that compared with the same period of
last year Pudong's industrial output value from January through
June totaled 63.388 billion yuan, up 17.2 percent. The fixed
assets investment stood at 14.734 billion yuan, representing an
increase of 42.8 percent. Meanwhile, the retail sales volume of
consumer commodities rose by 16.2 percent to 7.487 billion
yuan-worth.
</P>
<P>
Progress has also been made in foreign trade, with exports
increasing by 23.3 percent to 1.687 billion US dollars-worth in
the first half of the year, higher than the city's average.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Pudong's average per capita labor productivity has
been enhanced from 24,800 yuan at the beginning of the year to the
present 37,200 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Infrastructure construction has made great headway; a number of
key projects, including Pudong International Airport, the No.2
Subway Line and municipal public facilities are under way.
</P>
<P>
Significantly, Pudong signed another 313 foreign-funded
projects in the first half of the year, with investment totaling
2.654 billion US dollars, including 749 million US dollars-worth
of foreign funds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
