<HEADLINE> Waigaoqiao Sees Sharp Growth in Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The Waigaoqiao Bonded Zone in
Shanghai's Pudong New Area has reported a sharp increase in
foreign trade in the first half of this year, with a combined
trade volume of one billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
This figure is a growth of 114 percent over the same period of
last year, according to local customs statistics.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the zone's total exports rose 81 percent, to reach
262 million dollars-worth, and its import value came to 804
million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Waigaoqiao is the country's largest bonded zone, with a planned
area of 10 sq km.
</P>
<P>
The zone has always made efforts to develop its potential, and
to encourage processing industry over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investors now are allowed to do any kind of business
except commercial retail.
</P>
<P>
Specialists say that the zone's rapid growth of foreign trade
might continue till the end of this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
