<HEADLINE> Tianjin Pursues Electronic Banking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, July 21 (Xinhua) -- This port city in north China has
successfully put into operation an electronic network compatible
for cards issued by different banks.
</P>
<P>
Since January this year Tianjin has invested 30 million yuan in
linking the networking system of the major banks with that of the
local branch of the People's Bank of China, the central bank.
</P>
<P>
The local branches of the China Construction Bank and the
Agricultural Bank of China have already been linked electronically
to one another, and the other banks are expected to join the
network soon.
</P>
<P>
Once all the banks are linked up by the banking network,
holders of cards issued by any bank can pay into or withdraw from
deposits through any POS or ATM machine in Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the card network is to be linked up with those of
Visa International and Mastercard.
</P>
<P>
Since the local branch of the Bank of China issued the first
credit card, the Great Wall Card, in Tianjin in 1985, at least
another four types of cards have been issued by the Industrial and
Commercial Bank of China, the China Construction Bank, the
Agricultural Bank of China, and the Bank of Communications.
</P>
<P>
The latest statistics show that banks in Tianjin have issued a
total of 480,000 cards, including 380,000 credit cards and 100,000
ATM cards. Business transactions conducted with such cards reached
6.6 billion yuan-worth last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
