<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Southern Airlines to Be Listed in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 21 (Xinhua) -- China Southern Airlines Company
Limited, one of China's leading airlines, is to issue 1.03 billion
H shares, shares for major state enterprises from China's interior
areas, in Hong Kong soon, the company announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The new shares, to be issued at a subscription price between
3.71 and 4.70 Hong Kong dollars, are expected to raise up to 4.8
billion Hong Kong dollars (about 626 million US dollars) for the
air company.
</P>
<P>
Under the Global Offering, the Hong Kong Offering, the US
Offering and the International Offering are initially allocated 71
 million, 353.513 million and 573.287 million new H shares
respectively, said Steven Wisch, managing director of Goldman
Sachs (Asia) L.L.C., the sole global coordinator, sponsor and lead
manager of the Global Offering.
</P>
<P>
Yan Zhiqing, vice chairman and president of China Southern
Airlines, said at a press conference this afternoon that his
company plans to use about 283 million US dollars of the net
proceeds of the Global Offering to purchase new planes and related
flight equipment.
</P>
<P>
The remaining capital would be used to repay long-term debt,
purchase and install computerized flight operation and financial
management systems, finance the construction of facilities at new
airports in Haikou and Zhengzhou, and build an air-catering
facility at the company's route base in central China's Hubei
province, he added.
</P>
<P>
"As China's economy is growing, we see immense opportunities in
China's commercial aviation industry. With our strong presence in
the domestic market, we are well-positioned to capitalize on the
growth and further develop our business through expanding our
international operations," Yu Yan'en, chairman of the board of
directors of China Southern Airlines, was quoted as saying in a
press release to the local media.
</P>
<P>
Based in Guangzhou, capital of south China's Guangdong
province, China Southern Airlines is believed to be one of the
three largest air carriers in China, along with Air China and
Shanghai-based China Eastern Airlines.
</P>
<P>
The company's president Yan said that in 1996, the company
ranked number one among all Chinese airlines in terms of
passengers carried, number of scheduled flights per week, number
of hours flown and size of route network and aircraft fleet.
</P>
<P>
With a fleet of 88 aircraft, the company now operates a total
of 270 domestic routes serving 68 destinations in China, as well
as 47 international and regional routes.
</P>
<P>
Yan revealed that in the next three years, the company plans to
 invest some 10 billion RMB yuan (1.2 billion US dollars) to buy
aircraft and expand operation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
