<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Confers with Hungarian Finance Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing
held talks here today with Medgyessy Peter, chairman of the
Economy Commission and finance minister of Hungary.
</P>
<P>
Li said he believed Medgyessy's visit would help increase
mutual understanding and promote trade and economic
cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said China takes a positive attitude to developing ties with
Hungary in trade and economy, as well as other areas, and hopes
that both countries can make full use of their own advantages and
cooperate in various areas including commodity trade, mutual
investment and technology cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his hope for more exchanges between provinces
and cities of the two countries, and welcomed Hungarian
enterprises to cooperate with the central and western parts of
China.
</P>
<P>
Medgyessy said Hungary and China share many opportunities in
trade and economy, and Hungary is ready to develop long-term
relations with China in this area.
</P>
<P>
He said Hungary hopes to work with China to increase
information exchanges and strengthen mutual understanding, and
discuss the possibility of cooperation in energy, education,
aviation, finance and other sectors, as well as in the central and
western parts of China.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his congratulations on the achievements China
has made in social and economic development and on Hong Kong's
smooth return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Li thanked Medgyessy and said he hoped that Hungary could make
use of Hong Kong, which serves as a bridge between China and other
countries, to further develop trade and economic ties with China.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the meeting, Wu Yi, minister of foreign trade and
economic cooperation, met with Medgyessy and his party.
</P>
<P>
The Hungarian visitors arrived here July 19 at the invitation
of Li. 
</P>
