<HEADLINE> China Construction Bank Networks Credit Card System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The China Construction Bank will
link up its credit card systems in five cities starting from
tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
The networked credit card system will start operation first in
Beijing, Shanghai, Shenzhen, Guangzhou and Wuhan.
</P>
<P>
This means that any owner of the credit card issued by the
China Construction Bank, or the "Dragon Card," can make cash
withdrawals or get a checking account balance from the networked
Automated Teller Machines (ATM) in any of those cites.
</P>
<P>
And the link-up will shorten the time for cash withdrawal to
about eight seconds and that for checking an individual account
balance to about six seconds.
</P>
<P>
Instant settlement, faster authorization, and safety checking
will also be made possible since all the branch banks in the five
cities, as well as designated places that accept the Dragon Card,
including shops, will be hooked up to the network.
</P>
<P>
The bank also expects to connect the credit systems in another
26 cities to the network, and introduce new services to Dragon
Card users.
</P>
<P>
The number of Dragon Cards had expanded to 14.97 million by the
end of June, making it the second most-popular credit card in
China. The transaction volume for the cards totaled 159.8 billion
yuan for the first half of this year compared with the 157.4
billion last year. And 48,500 shopping centers currently accept
Dragon Cards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
