<HEADLINE> Enterprises Keen on Trademark Registration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, July 21 (Xinhua) -- It has become a common practice for
industrial and commercial enterprises in this city in east China's
Zhejiang province to promptly apply for trademark registration for
their new products.
</P>
<P>
So far, the city has registered nearly 10,000 trademarks, the
most in the country.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, with the rapid growth of the market
economy, more and more enterprises are standardizing their
economic operations in line with market economy laws, and have
come to know how to protect their legal rights and interests.
</P>
<P>
The business people here have become increasingly aware of
trademark registration, for it can effectively avoid economic
disputes and protect their rights and interests.
</P>
<P>
And a lot of old-style markets and stores have resorted to
trademark registration to protect their intangible assets.
</P>
<P>
In addition, more and more industrial and commercial
enterprises in the city have started to register trademarks
abroad.
</P>
<P>
To date, Ningbo enterprises have registered a total of 226
trademarks in 56 countries and regions worldwide.  
</P>
</TEXT>
