<HEADLINE> 52 Rebels Killed in East Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 21 (Xinhua) -- At least 50 Tamil rebels were
killed today when they attacked government troops in Eastern
province of Sri Lanka, according to a military spokesman here this
evening.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman, Ink Dewage, said the troops on patrol in
Batticaloa district this afternoon were attacked by a large group
of Tamil rebels with small arms and mortars.
</P>
<P>
The troops retaliated and their reinforcements engaged the
rebels from two directions, inflicting heavy casualties on the
rebels. The rebels fled westward carrying their casualties and
some of the dead, Dewage said.
</P>
<P>
The troops so far have recovered 37 dead bodies of the rebels
along with a lot of military equipment.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a war for a separate state
in the north and east of the country since 1983.  
