<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ronaldo's Transfer Issue to be Settled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, July 21 (Xinhua) -- FIFA on Tuesday will settle Ronaldo's
transfer dispute between Barcelona and Inter Milan at Zurich, it
was reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilan star will make soccer legal history if FIFA ratify
his move from Spanish side to Italy.
</P>
<P>
Ronaldo has paid Barcelona four billion pesetas (27.6 million
U.S. dollars) to let him go as a free agent, which is based on his
contract with Barcelona on payment of a 28 million U.S. dollars
penalty.
</P>
<P>
However, Barcelona doesn't allow Ronaldo to move to a foreign
club. Inter Milan argues that once a player becomes a free agent
in his own country he is free to join a club in another country.
</P>
<P>
Ronaldo expected to play for Inter Milan against English
champions Manchester United in a friendly next weekend.
</P>
<P>
After a couple of weeks dispute with Inter Milan, Barcelona
seemed to accept Ronaldo's leaving. The club has reportedly made a
13 million dollar bid for Brazilian side Flamengo's 23-year-old
Savio Bortolini Pimentel.  
</P>
