<HEADLINE> Nadamu Sports Fair Opens in Inner Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, July 21 (Xinhua) -- A grand-scale sports fair, known as
"Nadamu" in Mongolian, was kicked off today to mark the 50th
anniversary of the establishment of the Inner Mongolia Autonomous
Region.
</P>
<P>
Nadamu, which means "entertainment and games" in the Mongolian
language, has a tradition of more than 700 years. Throughout the
history of the event, horse racing, archery and Mongolian
wrestling have been three major activities.
</P>
<P>
Zou Jiahua, vice-premier and head of the delegation of the
central government, attended the opening ceremony this
morning together with other delegation members.
</P>
<P>
Such fairs are normally held throughout the grasslands in
summer or autumn seasons when flowers are blooming, the grass is
green, and the cattle and sheep are well-fed.
</P>
<P>
This year's four-day Nadamu will include the traditional sports
events as well as camel racing, Mongolian chess and martial arts.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the sixth Inner Mongolian international horsemanship
contest will be held.
</P>
<P>
Ulgi, chairman of the Inner Mongolia regional people's
government, declared the fair's opening in the well-decorated
Inner Mongolia Horse-racing Venue.
</P>
<P>
Cheered on by the audience, the regional horsemanship team gave
an outstanding performance. Wrestling, horse racing, and archery
competitions followed.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Zou Jiahua granted awards to the winning
wrestlers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
