<HEADLINE> Macao-Manila Air Route Inaugurated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Air Macao opened a new air route
today linking Macao and Manila, capital of the Philippines,
bringing the total number of its air routes to nine.
</P>
<P>
The airline company will have two flights to Manila weekly, on
Monday and Friday respectively. Each single flight takes about one
hour and 50 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Following the opening of the new air route, the airline's
weekly flights rose to 102.
</P>
<P>
Founded in April 1994, Air Macao has built up a fleet of six
Airbus planes, and opened up regular flights to Beijing, Shanghai,
Kaohsiung, Taipei, Qingdao, Xiamen, Wuhan and Bangkok.
</P>
<P>
Wang Guixiang, chairman of the board of directors of the air
company, said today in a reception marking the opening of the new
air route that his company has begun to make profits over the
past few months.
</P>
<P>
The airline transported some 660,000 passengers last year. The
number surged to 500,000 in the first half of the year, and would
probably reach one million by the end of the year, Wang predicted.
</P>
</TEXT>
