<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- A highly organized Lusaka-London
drug syndicate masterminded by a well-known Lusaka businessman
has been smashed, Times of Zambia reported today.
</P>
<P>
Eleven people including three sons of the businessman have
been arrested respectively at Gatwick Airport in London and
Lusaka International Airport, confiscating drugs valued at about
0.44 million U.S. Dollars, said the local newspaper.
</P>
<P>
Three others including the businessman's two other sons are on
the run and a manhunt has been launched.
</P>
<P>
At the Gatwick Airport three Zambians including one son of the
businessman were arrested together with three Britons and a man
from Democratic Republic of Congo.
</P>
<P>
A female employee at an airport duty-free shop and two other
sons of the businessman were caught at Lusaka Airport together
with a British national when they tried to smuggle 16 bars of
hashish of drug. 
