<HEADLINE> HK Civil Service to Maintain Efficiency: Secretary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The civil service of Hong Kong
will maintain its high efficiency and teamwork spirit, and
contribute to Hong Kong's continued prosperity, said Lam
Woon-Kwong, Secretary for the Civil Service of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (HKSAR).
</P>
<P>
"Stability is key to prosperity and development, and the
stability of the civil service is the foundation of social
stability in Hong Kong," Lam was quoted as saying by today's local
media.
</P>
<P>
He said that the 180,000 members of the local civil service
were well prepared for the historic return of Hong Kong to China
on July 1, and have adapted quickly to their new role as employees
of the HKSAR government.
</P>
<P>
He noted that on July 3, the first work day for the
newly-established HKSAR government following a five-day public
holiday, all government departments maintained normal operation
and underwent no change except for their names.
</P>
<P>
While the existing civil service has no problem of confidence,
he said, there are also many people who want to join the
government service, with nearly 15,000 people taking part in the
latest examination for the recruitment of some 40 administrative
officers.
</P>
<P>
Calling high efficiency, flexibility and ability to work under
pressure "major characteristics and fine tradition of Hong Kong's
civil service", Lam said that he is quite confident in the morale,
teamwork spirit, efficiency and quality of the civil servants
after Hong Kong's return to China.
</P>
<P>
He also praised the excellent performance of the civil service
contingent in relevant work concerning the Hong Kong handover
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
"Now we have started to prepare for the World Bank conference
due in September," he said. "With the experience acquired from the
handover ceremony, I believe we are able to handle whatever
situation." 
</P>
</TEXT>
