<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar ended
stronger today in Sydney, but the currency had edged back from its
earlier highs which had been inspired by rise in the price of gold
during New York trading on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar ended at 74.13 US cents, from 73.89
locally late Friday.
</P>
<P>
