quarterly price index data due Wednesday as to what the Reserve
Bank of Australia will do," said a Macquarie Bank foreign exchange
trader.
</P>
<P>
Rothschild foreign exchange trader Paul Macarounas said there
were some talks on the market that the central bank might ease
policy and cut the 5.5 percent cash rate as early as this Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar was at 85.66 Japanese yen, from 85.45
yen, and at 1.3177 German marks, from 1.3244 marks in Sydney
previously.  
</P>
