<HEADLINE> China Builds More Expressway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 21 (Xinhua) -- China had built 3,253 kilometers
of expressways by the end of 1996, compared with only 50 km in
the early 1990s, Guangming Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
They are located in a dozen provinces and cities including
Beijing, Tianjin and Shanghai municipalities and Shandong,
Liaoning and Guangdong provinces.
</P>
<P>
According to the national development plan for the 1996-2000
period, the country will give priority to the construction of
high-grade roads.
</P>
<P>
The length of expressways is expected to reach 6,500 km by the
year 2000, when a national network of expressways will have taken
shape, the paper said.  
