<HEADLINE> Chinese Electronics Giant To Computerize Management </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The TCL Holdings Corporation
Limited, one of the largest electronics manufacturers in China,
has signed an agreement with a local firm in Beijing to develop
software to modernize its management.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, TCL will pay 60 million yuan for the
project and the Beijing Case Software Technology Company Ltd., the
supplier of the managerial software, will provide TCL with a
package of software products and technology.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that a Chinese company has invested huge
sums to computerize its management system, according to local
observers.
</P>
<P>
They agreed that such cooperation will be of great significance
for Chinese firms interested in modernizing their management and
will also benefit the development of the country's software
industry.
</P>
<P>
TCL ranks first among domestic telephone producers and third
among TV set manufacturers.
</P>
<P>
Case, a subordinate company under the Chinese Academy of
Sciences, is one of the most successful software producers in the
country, especially in software concerning enterprise management
and office work.  
</P>
</TEXT>
