<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Rise on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continue to rise
sharply on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index recovered by 26.52 points to close at 1,950.75
points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased to 153.1 million units,
valued at 393.21 million Singapore dollars (about 269.32 million
US dollars). Advances outnumbered declines by 218 to 123, while
289 other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Asiamatrix was the most actively traded stock as it registered
a turnover of 15.16 million units. It was followed by local
bookstore Popular which had 8.58 million shares traded. Asia Food
&AMP; Properties was next with 6.91 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
GE Life led the gainers of the day as it rose by 90 cents to
end at 19.9 Singapore dollars. The United Overseas Bank (UOB)
Foreign gained 70 cents to finish at 16.1 Singapore dollars, while
the Development Bank of Singapore (DBS) Foreign closed 40 cents
higher at 19.5 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, City Developments Warrant 98 was the biggest
loser as it declined by 70 cents to finish at 11 Singapore
dollars. The Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign fell by 30
cents to close at 28.3 Singapore dollars, while Thai Prime Fund
ended 25 cents lower at 9.55 US dollars.  
</P>
