<HEADLINE> Two German Banks Plan to Merge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The Munich-based Bayerische
Hypotheken und Wechselbank AG and the Bayerische Vereinsbank AG
announced today that they would form Germany's second biggest
commercial bank.
</P>
<P>
The merger, with the consent of the insurance giant Allianz, a
major shareholder in both banks, still needs to be approved by the
cartel office.
</P>
<P>
The new bank, Bayerische Hypo und Vereinsbank AG, will have a
balance sheet of 743 billion marks (about 415 billion
U.S. dollars) in total, second only to Deutsche Bank's 866 billion
marks.
</P>
<P>
Allianz will hold 15 percent of the new bank, it is reported.
</P>
<P>
The Vereinsbank and the Hypotheken und Wechselbank are at
present the country's fourth and fifth largest commercial banks.
</P>
