<DOCNO> XIE19970721.0097 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 159 People Die of AIDS in Philippines Since 1984 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- A total of 916 AIDS cases have been
reported in the Philippines including 159 deaths since 1984 to
June this year, the Philippine Health Department said today.
</P>
<P>
Of the total AIDS (acquired immunodeficency syndrome) cases,
668 were transmitted through sex, the department said in a report.
Others were transmitted by infected blood, injecting drug use and
from infected mothers to infants.
</P>
<P>
Sexual transmission continues to be the number one mode of
transmitting AIDS virus in the country, with 14 new cases recorded
by the department in June as sex-related infection, it said.
</P>
<P>
The report further said that the age group at highest risk was
20-39 years, considered to be the most productive and most
sexually active.
</P>
<P>
Health Secretary Carmencita Reodica stressed in the report that
the only way to lessen the growing number of AIDS cases is to be
responsible for one's sexual behaviors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
