<HEADLINE> Suspected Arson at Foreigners' Home Injures 21 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 21 (Xinhua) -- A suspected arson fire at a home for
foreigners broke out around midnight in the German town of Essen,
injuring 21 people, including a baby and four children, said
reports reaching here this morning.
</P>
<P>
The four-story building in central Essen housed over 100
people, most of them asylum seekers. Police said that no evidence
was available so far to show the fire was started by people who
hate foreigners.
</P>
<P>
Initial investigations found that unidentified persons set two
sofas on fire in an upper-story stairwell of the home. The fire
has made the building uninhabitable.  
</P>
