<HEADLINE> More Banks to Join Interbank Money Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Another 27 urban cooperative
banks will soon join the Shanghai-based national interbank money
lending and borrowing center, according to a center source.
</P>
<P>
The source said that the latest 27, approved by the People's
Bank of China, the central bank, will bring the membership of the
money market to 54.
</P>
<P>
The new members include urban cooperative banks in
Shijiazhuang, Jinan, Zhengzhou, Hangzhou, Qingdao, Xiamen, Hefei,
Harbin, Guiyang, Ningbo, Shenyang, Xi'an and Changsha.
</P>
<P>
Through the interbank money market, the member banks can deal
in lending, borrowing, bond repurchases, and spot bond trading.
</P>
<P>
Analysts say that as more rules and regulations are issued by
the central bank, China's interbank and bond markets are
undergoing healthy and stable development. 
</P>
