<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wang Junxia Pulls out of World Athletics Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 21 (Xinhua) -- China's Olympic 5,000 meters
champion Wang Junxia has decided to pull out of the 6th World
Athletics Championships starting on August 1 in Athen even if the
IAAF might give her a wild card, an official from the Chinese
Athletics Association said here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Wang, who won the 5,000 meters gold medal plus a silver for the
10,000 meters last year in Atlanta, was not included on the list
of the 27-member Chinese team which was formed today.
</P>
<P>
"She quit training after the Olympics and took part in no
competitions since last October. We heard that she was bothered by
a constant headache and some other private problems. Her coach
hopes she can come back next year," said Shang Xiutang, Secretary-
general of the CAA.
</P>
<P>
It was learned that the 23-year-old world 10,000m record holder
still hates her former coach Ma Junren, who guided her to win the
world 10,000m gold medal at the 1993 World Championships in
Stuttgart. Ma, who helped Qu Yunxia, Liu Dong and Wang win three
golds in Stuttgart, still refuses to give Wang the car she earned
as a gift at the meet.
</P>
<P>
Without Wang, China's best hope for this year's championships
is to win a bronze medal. Huang Zhihong, former Olympic and world
women's shotput winner, Gao Hongmiao, last year's World Cup
women's 10 kilometers walk gold medalist and Ren Xiujuan, who
currently ranks world 9th with a 14.66m performance in the women's
triple jump, are China's medal hopefuls. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
