<HEADLINE> New Joint Foreign Trade Venture in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Lansheng Daewoo Co. Ltd, a joint
venture between China and the Republic of Korea (ROK), will open
here soon.
</P>
<P>
It will be funded by the Shanghai Lansheng Group and the Daewoo
Corporation, and is the second Sino-foreign joint venture
authorized by the Chinese Government to try out foreign trade in
Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Lansheng Daewoo will have a registered capital of 100 million
yuan, with the Lansheng Group contributing 51 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
According to a preliminary development plan, by the year 2000,
the joint venture will handle two billion U.S. dollars worth of
imports and exports a year.
</P>
<P>
It is registered in the Pudong New Area, and is significant for
Pudong's development and opening-up drive and useful for
increasing the market penetration of Chinese commodities into the
international market. 
</P>
