<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Some 50 U.S Green Beret soldiers
will arrive in Uganda within 48 hours to train a 800-men Uganda
unit for peacekeeping purpose.
</P>
<P>
The U.S soldiers are part of a 120-member special forces which
are to train Senegalese soldiers in about two months.
</P>
<P>
The 120 Americans will depart today from their base in Fort
Bragg, North Carolina, reported The Monitor today.
</P>
