<HEADLINE> Zambia to Re-set Minimum Wages for Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government is
organizing a tripartite meeting with the labor movement and
employers to re-set minimum wages for workers following a recent
discovery of slave conditions for employees in some firms.
</P>
<P>
Times of Zambia today quoted Labor Minister Peter Machungwa as
saying at the end of his tour of some Lusaka firms that the
meeting will review the current minimum wages, which has not been
adjusted for many years.
</P>
<P>
The minister promised to protect these people at the lower end
by all means from exploitation.
</P>
<P>
Economic liberalization does not mean leaving workers' plight
to "the whims of inhuman investors", he said. 
