<HEADLINE> US-made Warship Goes on Auction Block </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 21 (Xinhua) -- An old US-made warship will be
sold to the highest bidder tomorrow following a ruling by a local
court in China's largest metropolis Shanghai to auction off the
ship.
</P>
<P>
The landing ship will go on the auction block on the local ship
exchange because its owner, a Shenzhen company, is unable to pay a
Shanghai shipbuilder the cost of updating the ship into a yacht.
</P>
<P>
The ship was first given as a gift to the Kuomintang navy after
it was built in New York in 1942. It had been in the possession of
the People's Liberation Army since 1949, until it was
decommissioned two years ago. It was sold to the Shenzhen company
in the same year.
</P>
<P>
The No. 1 Intermediate People's Court in Shanghai has entrusted a
local auction firm to handle the auction. 
</P>
</TEXT>
