<HEADLINE> Huge BOC Loan to Major TV Manufacturer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China, the nation's
leading foreign exchange bank, has decided to extend 3.8 billion
yuan in loans to the Konka (Group) Co. Ltd., a state-owned major
TV set manufacturer in China.
</P>
<P>
The loans are the biggest the bank has ever extended to Chinese
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Konka, based in Shenzhen, Guangdong Province, will use the
loans to expand its production capacity, increase its domestic and
overseas market shares, and establish its product as an
internationally recognized name brand.
</P>
<P>
The Konka group is a blue chip company listed on the Shenzhen
Stock Exchange, and also one of 300 top enterprises enjoying
government support. It earned over five billion yuan from sales
last year.
</P>
<P>
The company produced 2.3 million color TV sets last year,
taking up 13 percent of the domestic market. It is expected to
turn out 3.5 million units this year, and five million by the end
of this century, when its earnings from sales will reach ten
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey shows that more than 65 percent of the domestic
market of color TVs are China-made name brands, including
Changhong, Konka and TCL King.
</P>
<P>
Experts with the Ministry of the Electronics Industry predicted
that the domestic sales of color TVs will grow about 20 percent to
20 million units this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
