<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Magurchhara Gas Well Fire Intensifies in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The gas-ignited fire intensified in
Magurchhara Gasfield in northern Bangladesh while the leakage of
gas through "hundreds of points" around the gas well has created
panic in the area, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The fire situation deteriorated from Saturday morning during
the preparation work at the New Drilling Pad. A sudden heavy
pressure of gas was observed at the worksite and more new gas
leakage points have developed in the new areas.
</P>
<P>
Occidental Bangladesh Ltd., a United States company which has
been operating at the gas well since the gasfield fire erupted on
June 15, has stopped its work there and remove all men from the
worksite.
</P>
<P>
Occidental officials have also marked an one kilometer area as
"very risky", and warned the people of "serious consequences".
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Bangladesh Railway Saturday suspended all train
services running through the Magurchhara gas well area due to the
sudden intensification of the fire.
</P>
<P>
Drilling of the "relief well" which was scheduled to begin this
week to douse the fire will now be delayed further, said an
official of Occidental, adding that more experts from Singapore
and Canada would come to evaluate the present condition.
</P>
<P>
They are afraid if they proceed with the work, further gas
might come out suddenly from various points that may cause a
severe damage to wealth and life.
</P>
<P>
The government said in a statement Sunday that the people
should not be afraid of the measures being taken by the Occidental
for the sake of safety in the gasfield area.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
