<HEADLINE> Laid-off Workers Gets Help in Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The city of Guangzhou has set
itself a goal to help 80,000 laid-off workers find new jobs this
year to raise the re-employment rate of redundant workers to above
65 percent.
</P>
<P>
To do so, the city is encouraging profitable enterprises to
employ more workers laid off by poorly managed companies, and the
government is set to provide financial assistance to those
employers.
</P>
<P>
The city has also set limits to employment of people coming in
from other parts of the country in certain sectors to provide more
job opportunities for locals.
</P>
<P>
Government sources say that more than 30 million yuan (about
3.8 million US dollars) will be spent on the city's re-employment
project this year.  
