<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Drafts Framework for Enterprises Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Russia's Economic Ministry has
drafted an framework for enterprises reform in a bid to speed up
the nation's sluggish economic growth, the Interfax news agency
said today.
</P>
<P>
Under the framework, enterprises should first make efforts to
attract investors both from home and abroad, protect the interests
of all shareholders, and divide clearly the responsibilities
between the owners and the managements.
</P>
<P>
Specialists with the Economic Ministry agreed that the slow
speed of reforms in the Russian enterprises is the main obstacle
to the country's economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The specialists said that major problems with the enterprises
are inefficient management, lack of responsibility on the part of
leadership and lack of reliable financial information that are
helpful to their operations.
</P>
<P>
The framework, which has yet to be approved, also raised
concrete demands on enterprises, such as using international
standards to work their bank accounts. Enterprises that meet the
demands contained in the framework would be given priority in
winning government investment, they said.
</P>
<P>
If approved by the government, the specialists added, the
framework would serve as the basis for reform that would transform
unproductive old enterprises into companies fit for the conditions
of market economy in the future.
</P>
<P>
The specialists concluded that under the framework, financial
information in the non-credit-providing sectors should be open to
the public so as to ensure the transparency in the economic
activities of the enterprises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
