<HEADLINE> India's Inflation Rate Falls to 52-Week Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 21 (Xinhua) -- India's annual rate of inflation
plunged to a 52-week low of 4.7 percent for the week ended July 5
from 5.9 percent in the previous week, The Times of India reported
today.
</P>
<P>
This sharp decline, which came as expected, was mainly because
the direct effect of last July's petroleum price hike on inflation
has been worn off.
</P>
<P>
The inflation during the corresponding week last year was above
the five percent mark at 5.79 percent.
</P>
<P>
The official wholesale price index (WPI) for "all commodities"
rose 0.2 percent to 325.0 during the week under review as against
324.5 the week before.  
</P>
</TEXT>
