<HEADLINE> Thailand, New Zealand to Hold Eco-tourism Forum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Thailand and New Zealand will hold
a forum on eco-tourism in Bangkok on Friday this week.
</P>
<P>
The forum is aimed at encouraging ideas and exchanging
practical experience and presenting ways in which some common
problems are overcome in eco-tourism and adventure operations.
</P>
<P>
Both Thailand and New Zealand face challenges in waste water
treatment, rubbish disposal in national parks, implementing and
maintaining safety standards in adventure tourism, and encouraging
new tourism products that are ecologically friendly.
</P>
<P>
In recently years, there has been a growing demand from
Thailand's traditional markets -- Europe and North America -- for
a genuine holiday experience that brings visitors closer to the
natural environment and local lifestyles.
</P>
<P>
While this demand is creating a growing market for eco and
adventure tourism products, it also brings about concern on the
increasing problems and preservation of tourism products for
future generations.  
</P>
