<HEADLINE> World Conference on Diabetes Opens in Finland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, July 20 (Xinhua) -- More than 9,000 researchers and
medical professionals from more than 120 countries and regions are
gathering here for the five-day 16th conference of the
International Diabetes Union, which opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Topics on the agenda include basic and clinic studies on the
potentially deadly disease, the nursing of diabetic patients, and
related social issues.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the event, 14 preparatory sessions of panel groups had
been held since mid-July among some European countries by using
the teleconferencing technology via satellite relay.
</P>
<P>
Panel discussions were centered on, among other subjects, the
use of insulin in treating diabetics, the disease among children
and youths, and related education and research efforts.
</P>
<P>
Diabetic cases have been on the rise in both the industrial and
developing world over recent years, and the total number of
patients around the world is believed to be over 100 million.
</P>
<P>
It has reportedly become the third biggest killer after cancer
and AIDS in the United States. 
</P>
