<HEADLINE> Drought Hits DPRK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Sustained high temperatures and
drought are devastating a large span of farm land in the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK).
</P>
<P>
The land already affected, according to press reports here
today, had amounted to hundreds of thousand of hectares by July 19.
</P>
<P>
The high temperatures and drought came together in June, and
continued into this month, which otherwise should have marked the
beginning of the rainy season in the country.
</P>
<P>
Recent days have seen temperatures hovering around 35 degrees
Celsius in some parts of the DPRK.
</P>
<P>
While the maize on the crop land is in the ear and therefore
hungry for water, low water levels are recorded at rivers and
reservoirs due to excessive sunshine and little rainfall.
</P>
<P>
People across the country, which was hit by severe floodings in
the past two years, are answering to the government's calls to
mobilize against the drought, said the reports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
