<HEADLINE> Foreign Trade Up in East China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Imports and exports in Qingdao, a
port city in east China's Shangdong province, were worth 2.4
billion US dollars in the first half of this year, up 31 percent
from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The city's overseas-funded firms have maintained their rapid
growth with imports and exports combined amounting to 1.7 billion
US dollars, 44 percent more than that for the same period last
year. The figure accounts for 71 percent of the city's total trade
volume.
</P>
<P>
Trade in processed goods with supplied materials came to 1.7
billion US dollars in the first half, a 73 percent increase.
</P>
