The group's premium income by the end of last month rose 40
percent to hit 42.8 billion yuan (5.2 billion US dollars),
accounting for 56.3 percent of the group's annual targeted volume.
</P>
<P>
The premium income from property insurance rose 9.4 percent to
21 billion yuan while that from life insurance increased 107.5
percent to 18.14 billion yuan and reinsurance income amounted to
3.68 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The product structure of the group also improved as the premium
income from motor insurance, enterprise and family property
insurance took large proportion in the group's total property
insurance premium income.
</P>
<P>
Ma said that PICC Group will take effective measures in the
second half of this year to prevent and erase risks in its
business operation.
</P>
<P>
He said the group will strive to perfect its risk management
system, enhancing risk evaluation and improving its management on
compensation.
</P>
<P>
During the first half of this year, the group paid 16.7 billion
yuan in compensation to victims of air crashes, explosions, and
floods.
</P>
<P>
Ma said the group will also improve its management of insurance
agents who brought 4.1 billion yuan of income for the group in the
January-June period.
</P>
<P>
And the group's internal supervision system will be improved
and more attention will be paid to the auditing, added the PICC
president. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
