<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Argentina Moves into First Place </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Argentina moved into first
place in South American qualifying for the 1998 World Cup, scoring
a 2-0 victory over visiting Venezuela on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
At Buenos Aires, Crespo scored in the 30th minute and Paz in
the 56th as Argentina (7-2-4) increased its points total to 25,
two points ahead of Paraguay (7-3-2), which stumbled to a 2-1
defeat by Chile (5-3-4).
</P>
<P>
Chile is fourth with 19 points after the victory facilitated by
its star striker Ivan Zamorano's two goals in the eighth and 47th
minutes.
</P>
<P>
Colombia (6-4-3), third with 21 points, stopped a five-game
winless streak in the World Cup play with a 1-0 victory over
visiting Ecuador.
</P>
<P>
The result left Ecuador (4-6-3) at the seventh spot with 15
points among the nine nations in the South American qualifying
zone.
</P>
<P>
Bolivia (4-3-5) kept its hopes of qualifying alive with a 1-0
victory over visiting Uruguay at La Paz. Bolivia now stood fifth
with 17 points, while Uruguay (4-6-2), eighth with 14 points,
virtually has no chance of reaching France.
</P>
<P>
The top four teams advance to the 32-nation tournament next
summer in France along with Brazil, the defending champion.
</P>
