<HEADLINE> Tornado Attacks Italy's Coastal Town </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, July 20 (Xinhua) -- A tornado hit Bibione, a coastal
town near the famous Italian city of Venice by surprise earlier
today, injuring more than 40 people.
</P>
<P>
The tornado overturned or washed ashore more than 90 boats and
ships, and damaged over 250 cars. Along its way, it also ripped
away some roofs and uprooted some trees.
</P>
<P>
It caused a power outage and a temporary halt to the local
water supply, said media reports. 
