<P>
BONN, July 20 (Xinhua) -- World record holder Colin Jackson
recorded his best time of the season in the 110 meters hurdles at
a meeting in Ingolstadt on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Briton, who set a world record of 12.91 in Stuttgart in
1993, won the race in 13.24 seconds ahead of Germany's Falk Balzer
who finished second in 13.46. 
</P>
