<HEADLINE> Saudi Athlete Stripped of Medals for Doping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, July 20 (Xinhua) -- A Saudi Arabian athlete was
stripped of his gold and silver medals in the Pan Arab Games here
on Sunday after being disqualified for doping.
</P>
<P>
The Arab Sports Federation said in a statement that discus gold
medal winner Khaled al-Khalidi tested positive for an unspecified
drug in a Paris laboratory.
</P>
<P>
It was the first time that an Arab athlete was stripped of his
trophies since the games were inaugurated in 1953 in Alexandria,
Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Khalidi won the discus gold with a throw of 54.90 meters on
Monday and took the silver in the shot-put with a throw of 17.64
meters on Tuesday. 
</P>
