<HEADLINE> Nigeria Plans New National Theater in Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 20 (Xinhua) -- With all the ministry headquarters
having moved to the capital Abuja, Nigeria is considering
construction of a new national theater there.
</P>
<P>
Jimmy Atte, general manager of the current national theater in
the former capital Lagos, said here today a proposal has already
been presented to the federal government.
</P>
<P>
A plot, covering an area of 22,629 hectares or 226,289 square
meters, has been given for the new national theater, he said.
</P>
<P>
Unlike the one in Lagos, the proposed theater in Abuja is
locally designed to blend with the rocky hills of Zuma and Aso
Rocks, both famous tourist attractions in Abuja and its environs,
and to take the shape of a military beret cap, the general
manager said.
</P>
<P>
The current national theater was designed by Bulgaria and
looks like a military/police cap. The single-building complex is
one of the most modern structure in this economic center of the
country.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the proposed theater is to be in four buildings for
easy administration and maintenance and will be much smaller.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the design has also taken into consideration the
peculiarities of th country's various cultural domains and
special requirements.
</P>
<P>
The multi-functional theater will also be used for
conferences, musical concerts, drama, dances, meetings, fashion
and film shows, beauty pageants, exhibitions, important national
and international events, as well as other social and cultural
activities, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
