<HEADLINE> EC Decides to Sponsor Research Projects on TSE </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 20 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission has
recently decided to support eight research projects on
transmissible spongiform encephalopathies (TSEs), it was learned
here today.
</P>
<P>
The European Union's executive agency decided to provide 8.8
million ECUs (about 11.5 million U.S. dollars) within the
so-called FAIR program for agriculture, agri-industry and
fisheries.
</P>
<P>
These projects will involve participation by nine EU member
states, three countries associated with the FAIR program --
Norway, Iceland and Israel -- and Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
The eight projects were reportedly chosen in response to a call
for tenders published by the Commission on December 17 of last
year.
</P>
<P>
These projects constitute the first initiative within the
framework of the action plan on TSEs presented by the Commission
on November 13, 1996.
</P>
<P>
The selected projects will focus on the development of rapid
diagnostic tests in live animals, in the pre-clinical phase of the
disease, as well as in slaughtered animals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
